This code should work but is not fully tested

You can build it with ./auto-build.sh
Remembber to edit auto-build.sh to have your paths to mysql and cunit.

sqlite3 should work as well be hasn't been tested.


Unit tests can be run using make check. The following options can be passed to configure to point the tests at a database to use and to enable cunit.

--with-cunit=/usr/local
--with-dbname=test
--with-dbhost=test1
--with-dbpass=""
--with-dbuser=root
